Current pass advanced the branch but did not reach completion.

I fixed the offline dependency-cache mismatch in [Cargo.lock](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-github-gate-evaluators/cli/Cargo.lock) by aligning locked crate versions to what exists in the local Cargo cache, and I tightened the GitHub-gate slice so actionable `gh` failures are preserved through status/TUI rendering instead of collapsing into “missing PR” in [app.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-github-gate-evaluators/cli/src/app.rs), [github.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-github-gate-evaluators/cli/src/github.rs), [state.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-github-gate-evaluators/cli/src/state.rs), and [tui.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-github-gate-evaluators/cli/src/tui.rs). I also updated the related tests in [app.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-github-gate-evaluators/cli/tests/app.rs), [github.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-github-gate-evaluators/cli/tests/github.rs), [state.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-github-gate-evaluators/cli/tests/state.rs), [tui.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-github-gate-evaluators/cli/tests/tui.rs), and [cli.rs](/tmp/calypso-worktrees/feat-cli-github-gate-evaluators/cli/tests/cli.rs). `cargo fmt --all` passes.

Validation is still blocked by the sandbox: after dependency resolution was fixed, `cargo test` and even a direct `rustc --emit=metadata` fail with `Invalid cross-device link (os error 18)` while writing `.rmeta` files. That means I could not get any of the required Rust test suites to execute, so I did not commit and I did not update the PR checklist or local tracking docs after this increment. Local `main` does not show merge conflicts against this branch.
